1. Ja sam *verovala* da će doći na vreme. (I believed that he/she would come on time.)
2. Ona je *verovala* da će pobediti na takmičenju. (She believed that she would win the competition.)
3. Kada sam *verovala* da je istina, shvatila sam da sam pogrešila. (When I believed that it was the truth, I realized that I was wrong.)
4. Ti bi trebalo da si *verovao* u sebe i svoje sposobnosti. (You should have believed in yourself and your abilities.)
5. Mi smo *verovali* da će vreme biti lepo, ali smo se prevarili. (We believed that the weather would be nice, but we were wrong.)
6. Vi ćete *verovati* u ono što želite da verujete. (You will believe in what you want to believe.)
7. Oni su *verovali* da će biti lako, ali su se suočili sa izazovima. (They believed that it would be easy, but they faced challenges.)

Note: The word "verovala" is the past tense form of the Serbian verb "verovati" which means "to believe" in English. The star (*) is used to highlight the word as requested.